A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Joseph Marion Binns; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Joseph Marion Binns on January 5, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Joseph Marion Binns was born on July 13, 1942, in Columbus, Georgia, a
5 beloved son of Alice and Dr. Joseph Binns Sr.; and
6 WHEREAS, he served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and liberty with the United
7 States Army Reserves, valiantly and courageously protecting his fellow Americans as an
8 Airborne Demolition Specialist; and
9 WHEREAS, in 1983, Joseph Marion Binns relocated to Columbus, where he established
10 Southern Relocation Services, a commercial moving business that operated across the
11 southeastern United States, managing large-scale moves efficiently and reliably; and
12 WHEREAS, after returning to Atlanta in the 1990s, he expanded Southern Relocation
13 Services to handle commercial projects along much of the East Coast; and
