17 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife of 57 years, Carol, and was
18 blessed with three remarkable children, Anthony, Joseph III, and Ward, as well as five
19 wonderful grandchildren, Grayson, Nathan, Isabelle, Daniel, and Josephine; and
20 WHEREAS, he gave inspiration to many through his high ideals, morals, and deep concern
21 for his fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding he demonstrated to his
22 family and friends were admired by others; and
23 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
24 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
25 made this world a better place in which to live; and
26 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Joseph Marion Binns will long be
27 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
28 had the great fortune of knowing him.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
30 join in honoring the life and memory of Joseph Marion Binns and express their deepest and
31 most sincere regret at his passing.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
33 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
34 Joseph Marion Binns.
